#Memes of 2020 Find Some Levity In Our Current Existence, By Justin Kirkland - Nov 2, 2020

Can you imagine a reality where historians might look at our memes to suss out exactly why we are the way we are? It happens! Sociologists and anthropologists have spent centuries exploring who we are as humans through their various means of communication.

When they get to 2020, the memes will say that we were in a bit of an existential crisis. They’ll speculate that the internet, this digital playground of ours, has made us so unable to communicate in person that we have to repackage pop culture without context to make sense of our times. 

From serious news stories to frivolous celebrity drama, memes have given our daily assault of reality some much-needed moments of levity. They also have gotten really freaking weird this year. Be it politics, health, or cake, the memes of 2020 have been a comfort in dark times. Long live the meme. May they forever reign.https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/a30613359/best-memes-2020/
